Certainly! You can calculate the total number of animals in a shelter by simply summing up the quantities of each type of animal. Here is a simple Java code snippet that accomplishes this:

```java
public class AnimalShelter {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Number of each type of animal in the shelter
        int numberOfCats = 15;
        int numberOfDogs = 10;
        int numberOfRabbits = 7;

        // Calculate the total number of animals
        int totalAnimals = numberOfCats + numberOfDogs + numberOfRabbits;

        // Print the result
        System.out.println("Total number of animals in the shelter: " + totalAnimals);
    }
}
```

This code defines three integer variables for the number of cats, dogs, and rabbits. It then calculates the total by adding these numbers together and prints the result to the console. When you run this program, it will output the total number of animals in the shelter.
